  "texts": [
    "Consistent with this notation, we have F L = F C L = {f 3, • • •, f l-2 }.We also suppress the standardised choice of anchor L, writing DrL [β] = Dr L C L [β].",
    "The boundary components of Σ L will always have the linear ordering induced by L, so that H L (p 0, p 1, p 2) = H L (p) with p κ = p S L κ for κ = 0, 1, 2.",
    "We also write t L κ:= t S L κ for the Tube-actions on these three boundary components.Two linksL 1 = (f 1, • • •, f k) and L 2 = (f ′ 1 • • •, f ′ l) are composable if ∂ f (L 1) = ∂ i (L 2) and the composite L 1 ∧ L 2:= (f 1, • • •, f k-1, f k, f ′ 3, • • •, f ′ l) is again a link.",
    "Being composable is not a symmetric relation.",
    "Note that the right strip of L 1 ∧ L 2 is the union of the right strips of L 1 and L 2."
